Resume Web Panel
Workflow
Read the user's resume or career notes first.
Identify the target role and strongest positioning.
Rewrite content for web display, not long-form resume reading.
Structure the page as:
Hero positioning
Key metrics
Core capabilities
Representative projects
Work timeline
Work methodology
Contact section
Prefer concise, outcome-focused language.
Use strong visual hierarchy and responsive layout.
Keep the final output usable as a local HTML file unless the user asks for a full app.
Writing Rules
Lead with what the person can solve.
Use numbers and outcomes where available.
Do not copy the resume verbatim.
Avoid vague self-evaluation unless tied to evidence.
Keep each section short enough for web scanning.
Design Direction
For management, training, operations, or project roles, prefer:

Personal capability dashboard
Web PPT style
Timeline plus metrics
System-building narrative
Avoid overly cute or decorative resume styles unless the user asks for them.
